Step 1: Fork the repository on GitHub
(Login to GitHub → Open git-lab-demo → Click Fork)

Step 2: Clone the forked repository
cd Desktop
git clone https://github.com/YourUsername/git-lab-demo.git
cd git-lab-demo

Step 3: Create a new branch
git branch feature-update
git checkout feature-update

Step 4: Modify a file
notepad main.py

(Add the following line)
print("Change made in feature branch")

Save and close the file.

Step 5: Add and commit changes
git add main.py
git commit -m "Updated file in feature branch"

Step 6: Push feature branch to forked repository
git push origin feature-update

Step 7: Create Pull Request on GitHub
(Open GitHub → Pull Requests → New Pull Request → Create Pull Request)

Step 8: Merge Pull Request
(Click Merge Pull Request → Confirm merge)

Step 9: Update local repository after merge
git checkout main
git pull origin main

Step 10: Verify merge
git status
git log
